    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n\r\n**Refer to Strategy 1 & 4**\r\n\r\n1. **Run and Observe:** Run the code and carefully read the first error message in the console log. Try to find the most useful information among the large error message.\r\n2. **Discuss Error Message:** What do you think the error message is telling you? Identify where in the code the issue is occurring. <br>\r\n2. **Use AI Assistance (if needed):** If the error message is unclear, go to Level 4 and ask the AI chatbot for help in understanding what part of the error message is the most important and what the error message means. <br>\r\n3. **Modify & Fix the Bug:** Adjust the code to resolve the issue.\r\n\t- **Hint:** There are multiple errors! Fix one error at a time, running the program after each change to check your progress.\r\n    \r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; color: black;\">\r\n<h5><strong>📝 Unit Guide</strong></h5>\r\n\r\nDocument your experience with this debugging strategy:\r\n- What worked? \r\n- What challenges did you face? \r\n- How did this strategy help? \r\n- When might it be most useful in the future?\r\n</div>",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\ndef turn_right():\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.turn_left()\n\ndef paint_step():\n  painter.paint(\"blue\")\n  painter.mov()\n  turn_right()\n  painter.move()\n  painter.paint(\"rainbow\")\n  painter.turn_left()\n  painter.move()\n\n\npaint_step()\npaint_step()\nleo = Painter()\n\n\n\n\n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
    "teacher_markdown": "Students should use Error Message Clarifications (Strategy 4).\r\n\r\nStudents analyze full traceback messages to locate and interpret issues."
